('business:1-1-role-of-business-enterprise:match:a6f0f6fa', 'business', 'business:1-1-role-of-business-enterprise', '1.1 Role of Business Enterprise', 'match', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which definition matches the key term “Strained relationships”?", "options": ["A non-financial risk where long working hours and business pressure damage personal relationships.", "An individual who takes the risk of setting up and running a business enterprise.", "Seeing an opportunity to provide a product or service that people are willing to buy.", "The ability to identify a gap in the market or a need that existing businesses are not meeting."]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "“Strained relationships” means: A non-financial risk where long working hours and business pressure damage personal relationships."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:exam:b90a72d3', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q2", "question": "For which of the following might Sundip & Sons'' business plan be useful?", "options": ["A — Calculating the share of the profit due to each of the three partners", "B — Complying with current legislation relating to business planning", "C — Identifying the resources needed to expand into the new market", "D — Obtaining additional finance from shareholders"], "caseStudy": "A mobile phone repairer, trading as Sundip & Sons, operates as a partnership. Its three partners have produced a business plan outlining their intentions to widen the services offered to include laptop and tablet repairs.", "hint": "Think about what a business plan actually helps a business to DO. Which of these options is a genuine role of a business plan?", "starter": "The answer is C because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: C — Identifying the resources needed to expand into the new market</h5><p><strong>Why C is correct:</strong> A key role of a business plan is to identify the resources a business needs to operate. Sundip & Sons are expanding into laptop and tablet repairs, so they need to identify what new equipment, skills, and potentially premises this requires. The plan helps them plan for this expansion systematically.</p><p><strong>Why the others are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A (Profit share):</strong> Profit sharing between partners is governed by the partnership agreement, not the business plan. The business plan outlines how the business will operate and grow — not how profits are distributed.</li><li><strong>B (Legislation):</strong> There is no legislation requiring businesses to produce a business plan. It is not a legal requirement — it is a strategic management tool.</li><li><strong>D (Finance from shareholders):</strong> A partnership cannot have shareholders — shareholders are part of limited companies. A business plan could help obtain a bank loan, but not shareholder finance in this context.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "C — Identifying the resources needed to expand into the new market."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:exam:a8d8e357', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'exam', 'mcq', 1, '{"num": "Q6", "question": "Which of the following would help Radi to reduce his level of risk?", "options": ["A — Becoming a sole trader", "B — Carefully planning all business activity", "C — Ignoring the needs of customers", "D — Making employees work long hours"], "caseStudy": "Radi owns Chimney Restore Ltd, a company he set up in 2018. The company has grown rapidly and now employs 12 workers. However, Radi is becoming increasingly concerned about the level of risk he faces as the owner of a rapidly growing business.", "hint": "Think about which option directly addresses the problem of risk — the core purpose of a business plan.", "starter": "The answer is B because..."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\"><h5>Answer: B — Carefully planning all business activity</h5><p><strong>Why B is correct:</strong> The primary purpose of a business plan is to reduce risk. By carefully planning, Radi can identify potential problems before they occur, ensure resources are in place, and set clear objectives for managing growth. This directly addresses his concern about the increasing level of risk.</p><p><strong>Why the others are wrong:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>A (Becoming a sole trader):</strong> Chimney Restore Ltd is already a limited company, which actually gives Radi the protection of limited liability. Becoming a sole trader would increase his personal financial risk (unlimited liability), not reduce it.</li><li><strong>C (Ignoring customers):</strong> Ignoring customer needs would lead to falling sales and reputation damage — this increases risk significantly, not reduces it.</li><li><strong>D (Long hours for employees):</strong> Overworking employees leads to poor morale, mistakes, high staff turnover, and potential legal issues. This increases operational and legal risk.</li></ul></div>", "modelAnswer": "B — Carefully planning all business activity."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:f447e4e4', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "A business plan would normally be written:", "options": ["Every month to keep it up to date", "A month after a business starts trading", "After a business has become established and competitors are known", "Before a business starts"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 3, "explain": "Correct: D. A business plan is written before a business starts (or when a major change is planned). Writing it after the business starts defeats the purpose of reducing risk and guiding early decisions."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:a497784f', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "A business plan will:", "options": ["Make sure the competitors know you are in business", "Identify the competitors of the business", "Put the competitors out of business", "Allow the competitors to see whether you need finance"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct: B. One key section of a business plan involves identifying who the competitors are and how the business will compete against them. It does not alert competitors to your existence or remove them from the market."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:f55f1a46', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "The purpose of identifying resources in a business plan is to:", "options": ["Make sure the required resources have been identified and where they will come from, so potential investors feel safer", "Make sure there is a list of some of the resources required", "Make sure each person involved knows what ''resources'' means", "Make sure resources required cost less than first thought"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Correct: A. Identifying resources in full — and explaining how they will be obtained — gives investors confidence that the owners have thought through how the business will operate. A vague list is not sufficient."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:aa580afa', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following is NOT in a business plan?", "options": ["The target market for the new business", "The objectives of the business", "The dates of birth of the business owners", "The known competitors of the new business"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct: C. Dates of birth of business owners are personal and irrelevant to running a business. A business plan includes the target market, objectives, and competitors — all of which are relevant to business decisions."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:b90a72d3', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "For which of the following might Sundip & Sons'' business plan be useful?", "options": ["Calculating the share of the profit due to each of the three partners", "Complying with current legislation relating to business planning", "Identifying the resources needed to expand into the new market", "Obtaining additional finance from shareholders"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct: C. A business plan helps identify the resources needed to operate. Sundip & Sons are expanding into laptop and tablet repairs, so they need to identify what new equipment, skills and premises this requires. Profit-sharing is governed by a partnership agreement, and there is no legal requirement to have a business plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:544670a3', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following would help Radi to reduce his level of risk as a business owner?", "options": ["Becoming a sole trader", "Carefully planning all business activity", "Ignoring the needs of customers", "Making employees work long hours"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct: B. Careful planning reduces business risk by identifying potential problems before they occur and ensuring resources, finance, and markets are all considered. The other options would increase risk or cause harm."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:64406d77', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Why is a business plan especially important for a new business?", "options": ["Because the owner needs something to show friends and family", "Because it guarantees the business will be successful", "Because it helps obtain finance and reduces the risk of failure before trading begins", "Because it tells competitors what the business plans to do"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct: C. A new business has no trading history, so it is especially important to plan carefully. The plan helps secure finance from banks (who will not lend without one) and reduces the risk of failure by forcing the owner to think through all aspects of the business."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:8e6a22cf', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Should information about the hobbies of the business owners be included in a business plan?", "options": ["Yes, to show the owners are well-rounded individuals", "Yes, because hobbies may be relevant to the business", "No, it is personal and irrelevant to running the business", "No, because it takes up too much space"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct: C. Hobbies are personal information and are not relevant to business decisions. A business plan should only include information that helps the business or its investors understand how the business will operate and succeed."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:c27fa4d6', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "A bank is considering whether to lend money to a new business. Which of the following would most increase the bank''s confidence?", "options": ["The business owner''s personal bank statements", "A detailed and well-researched business plan", "A list of the products the business wants to sell", "A signed letter from a friend of the owner"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct: B. A detailed business plan shows the bank that the owner has carefully considered all aspects of the business — market research, competitors, finance needs, and objectives. This gives the bank confidence the loan will be repaid."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:7fafaf3b', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which statement about a business plan is TRUE?", "options": ["Writing a business plan guarantees the business will succeed", "A business plan eliminates all risk from starting a business", "A business plan reduces risk but cannot eliminate it", "Only new businesses need to write a business plan"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 2, "explain": "Correct: C. A business plan reduces the risk of failure by making owners think carefully about all aspects of their business. However, it cannot eliminate risk entirely — unexpected events can still cause a business to fail even with an excellent plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:4091f726', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "SJ Salon last wrote its business plan when it opened in 2014. A national competitor is about to open nearby. What does this situation suggest about the need for a new plan?", "options": ["No new plan is needed because the original plan is still valid", "A new plan is needed because the competitive environment has significantly changed", "A new plan should only be written if the salon makes a loss", "A new plan is unnecessary because the salon has been profitable"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct: B. A business plan should be updated when there is a major change in the business environment. A new national competitor entering the local market is exactly this kind of significant change — it affects the salon''s target market, pricing, marketing, and strategic objectives."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:mcq:511e6d6d', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which of the following is the best definition of a ''business plan''?", "options": ["A thought or idea about what a business might do in the future", "A document detailing the product/service, how it will be financed, marketed, and evidence from market research", "A legal document required by law before starting a business", "A monthly report produced by a business showing its profits"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 1, "explain": "Correct: B. A business plan is specifically a document (not just a thought or idea) that details the product/service, finance sources, marketing approach, and market research findings. It is not a legal requirement and is not produced monthly."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:6a57af9c', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan should include information about the hobbies of the business owners."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "FALSE. Hobbies are personal and irrelevant to business decisions. A business plan covers business-relevant content only: the business idea, finance, marketing, market research, competitors, target market, and objectives."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:7eb7cc4d', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan should include details of what marketing is planned."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. Marketing is a core section of any business plan. It identifies how the business will attract customers, what price it will charge, how it will promote its products, and through which channels it will sell."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:64950eb0', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "Writing a business plan guarantees that a business will succeed."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "FALSE. A business plan reduces the risk of failure but cannot guarantee success. Unforeseen circumstances — economic downturns, unexpected competition, changing consumer tastes — can still cause a business to fail even with a thorough plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:df95578c', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan is normally written before a business starts trading."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. The business plan is typically produced before the business starts, or when a major change is planned. Writing it after trading begins means many risks may not have been considered at the critical start-up stage."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:19120a26', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan should include a list of the favourite books read by the business owners."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "FALSE. Titles of business books (or any personal reading material) are irrelevant to the business plan. Only business-relevant information — markets, finance, competitors, resources, objectives — belongs in the plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:e926f7c0', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A good business plan is necessary if a business hopes to obtain external finance from a bank."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. Banks and other external investors will rarely lend money without seeing a detailed business plan. It demonstrates that the owners have thought carefully about how the money will be used and how the loan will be repaid."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:9611530d', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan should include analysis of the competitors in the market."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. Identifying competitors — and explaining how the business will differentiate itself (e.g. lower prices, better quality, unique features) — is an essential part of the business plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:b85d5209', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "Once written, a business plan never needs to be updated."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "FALSE. A business plan should be reviewed and updated when significant changes occur — such as a new competitor entering the market, the business deciding to expand, or major changes in consumer demand."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:9a251bc6', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A description of the target market should be included in a business plan."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. Identifying who the business is selling to (age, gender, income level, location, etc.) is fundamental to the business plan. It shapes decisions about pricing, promotion, and distribution."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:fc343e31', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "The information about who is running the business is irrelevant to investors and can be left out of a business plan."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "FALSE. Investors and banks are much more likely to fund a business run by people with relevant experience. Details of the owners'' qualifications and business experience are an important part of the plan."}'::jsonb),
('business:1-2-business-planning:tf:b1305a36', 'business', 'business:1-2-business-planning', '1.2 Business Planning', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "A business plan helps to identify the resources a business will need to operate."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "TRUE. One of the key roles of a business plan is to identify what resources — equipment, premises, staff — the business requires. Without this, a potential investor may feel the business has not been properly thought through."}'::jsonb)
